# ── Go build outputs ──
bin/
dist/
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
*.out
coverage.html
coverage/
vendor/

# Go profiling
*.prof
*.pprof

# Go workspace (go.work.sum is generated — only go.work needs committing)
go.work.sum

# ── Node.js / Next.js ──
node_modules/
.next/
.turbo/
.vercel/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Generated code (fully regenerated by buf generate / forge generate) ──
#
# Everything under gen/ except go.mod/go.sum is re-created on every
# `forge generate` run. Ignoring the whole directory and negating the two
# files Go needs is cleaner than enumerating every suffix.
gen/
!gen/go.mod
!gen/go.sum

# Handler-level generated code — CRUD handlers, authorizers (Tier-1; forge
# regenerates these on every run).
handlers/**/*_gen.go
# NOTE: `handlers/**/*_gen_test.go` is intentionally NOT ignored. These
# `handlers_crud_gen_test.go` files start life as scaffolds with
# `FORGE_SCAFFOLD:` markers, but transfer ownership to the user the moment
# every marker is cleared (see `writeScaffoldFile`). Once user-owned they
# carry real assertions and MUST be committed — otherwise CI runs `forge
# generate` against the file's absence, re-emits the broken stub, and
# `go test ./...` fails on a fresh clone. Track the scaffold (forge will
# refresh it if the user hasn't customized it) and rely on the
# scaffold-vs-customized check inside the file to decide whether the user
# owns it.

# Middleware generated code — auth, tenant scoping
pkg/middleware/*_gen.go

# Service mocks (regenerated by forge generate).
#
# Anchor the patterns to the project root so they only match the Go
# handler-mock outputs at `/mocks/` and `/handlers/mocks/`. An
# unanchored `mocks/` rule also matches frontend mock directories
# (e.g. `frontends/<name>/src/mocks/scenarios/`), silently hiding new
# scenario files from git — see ADR 0002 on frontend scenarios.
/mocks/
/handlers/mocks/

# Auto-generated seed data and fixtures (regenerated by forge generate)
db/seeds/
db/fixtures/

# ── IDE ──
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ── Environment ──
# .env.example is the only env file that should be committed.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ── OS ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Logs ──
*.log

# ── Local data / state ──
# Never commit on-disk databases, Docker volumes, or temp dirs.
data/
tmp/
*.air.toml.bak

# ── Forge internal state ──
# .forge/ contains debug-session.json, caches, .forge/state/build-<env>.json
# (handoff from `forge build --push` to `forge deploy`), transient side
# renders (.forge/render/ holds `--explain-drift` diff inputs and legacy
# fork-era renders), and other runtime state. Two exceptions are
# negated back in and MUST be committed:
#   checksums.json  — tracks what forge generated so other developers'
#                     `forge generate` can detect user modifications.
#   friction.jsonl  — append-only generator-friction log written by
#                     `forge friction add`. Shared project state: it
#                     travels with the repo so friction recorded by any
#                     agent/developer survives worktrees and clones.
# Everything else under .forge/ is per-developer state and intentionally
# excluded by the broad children rule below.
#
# NOTE: this must be `.forge/*` (children), not `.forge/` (the dir):
# git cannot re-include a file whose parent DIRECTORY is excluded, so a
# `.forge/` + `!.forge/checksums.json` pair silently ignores
# checksums.json and it never gets committed. (Found the hard way in
# cp-forge — see its .gitignore fork note.)
.forge/*
!.forge/checksums.json
!.forge/friction.jsonl

# ── What NOT to ignore ──
#
# The following are scaffolded once by `forge new` and then owned by you.
# `forge upgrade` uses checksum protection (not .gitignore) to detect and
# preserve your edits. Commit them.
#
#   cmd/*.go            — entrypoints (package main)
#   pkg/middleware/*.go  — non-generated middleware (scaffolded, user-owned)
#   CHANGELOG.md         — project changelog
#   docs/                — ADRs, runbook, SLO definitions
#
# The following encode shared project conventions for LLM-driven
# development and are INTENTIONALLY committed:
#
#   .reliant/                           — forge-managed conventions, project metadata, skills
#   reliant.md / CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md  — user-owned project memory file (depends on --memory flag)
#   .cursorrules                        — project memory file (cursor format)
#   .github/copilot-instructions.md     — project memory file (copilot format)
#   .mcp.json                           — project-level MCP server config
#   .mcp.json.example                   — documentation of opt-in MCP servers
#
# Do not add these to .gitignore. If you need to keep local-only overrides,
# create a `.mcp.local.json` or similar and ignore that instead.